    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - ADJUSTMENTS - Door HINGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x16029203" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Door HINGE</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Adjustment procedures show driver side; passenger side procedures are the same.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Hinge procedures are the same for either front or rear cab doors.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1603854" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603854.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 149. Cab Door Hinge</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UPPER HINGE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LOWER HINGE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HINGE BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>4. CAB HINGE PILLAR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOCKING BOLT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slightly loosen upper hinge bolts and move door as required at upper door hinge to obtain
                proper door position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold door in place and tighten both upper hinge bolts at the cab hinge pillar location.
                Tighten bolts to 13 to 15 Lbf-ft (18 to 20 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slightly loosen lower hinge bolts and move door as required at lower door hinge to obtain
                proper door position.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hold door in place and tighten both lower hinge bolts at the cab hinge pillar location.
                Tighten bolts to 13 to 15 Lbf-ft (18 to 20 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Close door and check for proper fit. If further adjustment is required, repeat procedure.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
